Privacy and Legal Notice
1.1 Information, content, and data on this website
Information on this website and the LINK Cash Locator App* is provided for informational purposes only. While every effort is made to ensure the accuracy of any information or other material contained on this website, it is provided on the basis that the LINK Scheme and Link Scheme Holdings Ltd (and its members, either individually or collectively) accept no responsibility for any loss, damage, cost, or expense of whatsoever kind arising directly or indirectly from or in connection with the use by any person of any information or other material contained herein. You must seek independent professional advice before relying on any information contained herein; reliance is at your own risk.
Any use of the information or other material contained on this website and the LINK Cash Locator App* shall signify agreement to this provision.
* LINK Cash Locator App is available for both Apple and Android mobile platforms.
1.1.1 Privacy Notice and Cookies Policy
Your information will be held by Link Scheme Holdings Ltd (LSHL) and/or Link Scheme Ltd (LSL) as data controller (referred to in this Notice as “we” or “us”). This Privacy Notice and the
Cookies Policy
:
sets out the types of personal data we collect;
explains how and why we collect and use your personal data; and
explains the rights and choices you have when it comes to your personal data.
If you have any questions about the topics set out in this Privacy Notice, or want more details about how we may use your personal information, you can contact us using the following e-mail address:
DPO@link.co.uk
.
For the purposes of this Privacy Notice, '
Data Protection Law
' means the EU General Data Protection Regulation as it forms part of retained EU law in the UK (referred to throughout this Privacy Notice as the UK GDPR), the UK Data Protection Act 2018 and any other applicable national privacy legislation and guidance issued by data protection regulators.
Right to Object
: You have a legal right to object at any time to the:
use of your personal information for direct marketing purposes; and
processing of your personal information, which is based on our legitimate interests, unless there are compelling legitimate grounds for our continued processing.
1.1.2 Who we are
Link Scheme Holdings Ltd and Link Scheme Ltd (together, "LINK") are the operator and operating company of the LINK Scheme as set out in the Financial Services (Banking Reform) Act 2013.
1.1.3 How the law protects you
On 25
th
May 2018, the EU General Data Protection Regulation came into effect. It now forms part of retained EU law in the UK following the UK’s withdrawal from the EU as the UK GDPR.  This section sets out the ways in which your privacy is protected under applicable Data Protection Law in the UK.
Data Protection Law states that we are allowed to use your personal information only if we have a legal basis for doing so. This could be for one or more of the following reasons:
to fulfil a contract we have with you or in order to take steps at the request of you prior to entering into a contract;
to perform a task that is our legal duty;
to undertake processing that is in our legitimate interest (i.e., a business or commercial reason to use your data to support the operation of LINK Scheme). In assessing whether something is in our legitimate interests we have to take account of, and balance, our interests against your interests; and
when you consent to it.
1.1.4 Personal Data we collect and from where
This section tells you what personal data we may collect from you when you use our services, and what other personal data we may receive from other sources. The basis on which we use your personal data is also outlined below.
Information you may provide to us
You may provide personal data to us directly:
When you submit a query to us via the LINK Info function on our website.
When you submit a review request for Access to Cash in your community.
When you submit a complaint about LINK’s services including LINK’s role as a Co-ordinating Body for bank branch closures, whether this complaint is made directly to LINK or to LINK's Independent Assessor.
If you contact us by telephone.
In e-mails and letters.
If you are a consultant or advisor to us, in the course of you providing services to us.
When you use the LINK Cash Locator App to to find LINK ATMs, Post Offices and shops offering cash at the till.
If you attend LINK’s office premises, as we collect personal information about employees and contractors in the form of images from a CCTV camera system if you are in the field of vision of this system.
Information we may obtain about you from third parties
If you are an employee, agent, or subcontractor of a Scheme Member, we may receive personal data about you from or on behalf of a Scheme Member. This may include (amongst other things) your name, work or other e-mail address, work, or other telephone and/or mobile number and other contact details.
If you work for an agent or subcontractor of LINK, we may receive information about you from your employer or the entity which engages you to provide services to LINK. This may include (amongst other things) your name, work or other e-mail address, work, or other telephone and/or mobile number and other contact details.
If you submit a complaint or query to LINK's Independent Assessor, or are named in a complaint or query submitted by someone else to the Independent Assessor, we may receive information about you from the Independent Assessor.  This data will be used by LINK and the Independent Assessor to investigate the complaint. In each case, the personal data we collect about you from the Independent Assessor may include (amongst other things) your name, work or other e-mail address, work or other telephone and/or mobile number and other contact details and other personal information that may be included in your complaint.
The Independent Assessor is not part of LINK’s business but uses a LINK e-mail address for complaints, which keeps communications (and LINK complaints data) safe, within LINK’s electronic security system. LINK staff cannot access the Independent Assessor’s e-mails.
In the course of our business as the Operator of the LINK Scheme we may also receive information from third parties related to your use of the LINK ATM Network.  Please note that we will never receive full cardholder data (including the card number (the 'PAN'), name and expiry date (unless you send this to us) so this data is "anonymised" as we cannot identify you from the data.
We may, on occasion, receive the PAN data (without accompanying name or expiry data information) in order to assist with arbitration and fraud management. Unless you send us information which identifies you, this data is also "anonymised" as we cannot identify you from the data.
Where data is "anonymised" it does not fall within the scope of Data Protection Law as it is not personal information.
Where such information is personal information (for example, if you provide us with, or a third party provides us with, information such that we can identify you as being the subject of the data), then LINK will process that data in accordance with Data Protection Law on the grounds set out below.
Outside organisations providing us with "anonymised" data about you include:
The provider of LINK ATM transaction processing for the LINK Scheme.
Scheme Members including LINK ATM operators and your ATM card(s) issuer.
